.TH CODEX_EXEC_SERVER 1 "July 2026" "codex-cli 0.142.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
codex\-exec\-server \- [EXPERIMENTAL] Run the standalone exec\-server service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.EX
Usage: codex exec\-server [OPTIONS]

.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
[EXPERIMENTAL] Run the standalone exec\-server service
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config <key=value>
Override a configuration value that would otherwise be loaded from `~/.codex/config.toml`. Use a dotted path (`foo.bar.baz`) to override nested values. The `value` portion is parsed as TOML. If it fails to parse as TOML, the raw string is used as a literal.
.PP
Examples: \- `\-c model="o3"` \- `\-c 'sandbox_permissions=["disk\-full\-read\-access"]'` \- `\-c shell_environment_policy.inherit=all`
.TP
.B \-\-strict\-config
Error out when config.toml contains fields that are not recognized by this version of Codex
.TP
.B \-\-enable <FEATURE>
Enable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=true`
.TP
.B \-\-listen <URL>
Transport endpoint URL. Supported values: `ws://IP:PORT` (default), `stdio`, `stdio://`
.TP
.B \-\-disable <FEATURE>
Disable a feature (repeatable). Equivalent to `\-c features.<name>=false`
.TP
.B \-\-remote <URL>
Register this exec\-server as a remote environment using the given base URL
.TP
.B \-\-environment\-id <ID>
Environment id to attach to when registering remotely
.TP
.B \-\-name <NAME>
Human\-readable environment name
.TP
.B \-\-use\-agent\-identity\-auth
Use Agent Identity auth from CODEX_ACCESS_TOKEN for remote registration
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help (see a summary with '\-h')
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR codex (1)
